  "summary": {
    "as": "Passed House",
    "asOf": "2022-05-11",
    "date": "2022-05-16T18:22:19Z",
    "text": "Ukraine Comprehensive Debt Payment Relief Act of 2022\n\nThis bill requires the Department of the Treasury to make efforts to secure debt relief for Ukraine.\n\nSpecifically, Treasury must order U.S. representatives to international financial institutions to advocate for such institutions to (1) immediately suspend all debt service payments owed by Ukraine to the respective institution, (2) provide concessional financial assistance to Ukraine, and (3) provide economic support for refugees from Ukraine (including refugees of African descent) and the countries receiving such refugees.\n\nTreasury must also immediately pursue, through bilateral and multilateral frameworks, comprehensive debt payment relief for Ukraine from other governments and commercial creditor groups."
  },
